The property was originally built in the 1980's by Hillreed Homes, and the property occupies a quiet cul-de-sac position on this sought after development, conveniently placed within one hundred metres of a good selection of amenities on the Ashford Road at Bearsted including shops providing for everyday needs and medical centre, within a half a mile is the village green with its selection of Bistro pubs, library and main line railway station connected to London on the Victoria Line. Educationally the area is well served with the local infant and junior school being well regarded. Maidstone town centre is some two miles distant and offers a more comprehensive selection of amenities including a wider range of schools for older children. The M20/A20/M2/M25 and M26 motorways are also close by and offer direct vehicular access to both London and the Chanel Ports.

The accommodation is conveniently arranged on two floors and extends in all to in excess 1400 square feet, with the added benefit of gas fired central heating by radiators and UPVC replacement double glazing and comprises (with approximate room measurements) as follows:

ON THE GROUND FLOOR:

ENTRANCE PORCH: UPVC entrance door, glazed side panel.

ENTRANCE HALL: Radiator.

CLOAKROOM: Low level W.C. Hand basin. Fully tiled walls.

L-SHAPED LIVING ROOM: 17'4" x 14'10" (5.30m x 4.53m). Approached by double casement doors from hallway. Radiator. Fireplace with fitted living flame gas fire, display top. Double glazed sliding patio doors overlooking rear garden affording a western aspect.

DINING ROOM: 13'0" x 11'1" (4m x 3.38m). Staircase to first floor with decorative balustrade. Radiator. Window to front affording an eastern aspect.

KITCHEN/BREAKFAST ROOM: 11'10" x 9'5" (3.60m x 2.87m). Fitted with units having oak door and drawer fronts with Carrion working surfaces, comprising: one and a half bowl stainless steel sink unit with mixer tap, cupboards under. Range of high and low level cupboards with working surfaces incorporating four burner gas hob with extractor hood above and oven beneath. Plumbing for automatic washing machine and dishwasher. Window overlooking rear garden affording a western aspect. Radiator. Built-in storage cupboard. Door to side. Ceramic tiled floor.

ON THE FIRST FLOOR:

LANDING: Built-in linen cupboard with lagged copper cylinder. Access t o roof space.

PRINCIPAL BEDROOM: 14'0" x 10'0" (4.26m x 2.97m). Radiator. Range of wardrobe cupboards with central dresser unit.

EN-SUITE SHOWER ROOM: Raised shower tray. Wash hand basin. Low level W.C. Radiator. Tiled splashbacks.

BEDROOM 2: 11'3" x 11'3" (3.45m x 3.45m). Built-in wardrobe cupboard. Window to front affording an eastern aspect. Radiator.

BEDROOM 3: 9'3" x 8'2" (2.83m x 2.50m). Window overlooking rear garden, western aspect. Radiator.

BEDROOM 4: 9'1" x 7'0" (2.78m x 2.12m). Radiator. Window overlooking rear garden, western aspect.

BATHROOM: White suite, panelled bath with mixer tap. Pedestal hand basin. Low level W.C. Fully tiled walls. Radiator.

OUTSIDE: Attached double garage 18'3" x 17'0" (5.58m x 5.23m) with electric light and power, overhead storage, wall mounted gas fired boiler supplying central heating and domestic hot water throughout. Personal door to rear. Side pedestrian access. The rear garden is a particular feature of the property with walled and fenced boundaries, well stocked with shrubs, laid to lawn with patio enjoying a western aspect and a pleasant degree of seclusion. Front garden laid to lawn with hedged boundaries.

